document_data.Personality:
Razylymingeir was brave{{Cite dungeon/53/Steelheart|68}} and prone to emotion, likely to burst into tears when sad{{Cite dungeon/53/Steelheart|61}} and to seek furious revenge when aggrieved.{{Cite dungeon/53/Steelheart|56}}

She was fascinated by humans{{Cite dungeon/53/Steelheart|59}} If these companions deduced her true nature, she was polite and apologetic as she attempted to explain her actions.
{{Quote|''Come on, you're heroes, aren't you? You're not going to let a few [[orc]]s get in our way, are you?''|Razylymingeir, as Katelyn Brekstel}}

document_data.Relationships:
Razylymingeir opposed the [[Cult of the Dragon]].

Her parents were the steel dragons [[Forge (steel dragon)|Forge]] and [[Glimmerfang]]. Prior to their deaths, the three dragons lived together in human form in Darmshall, where Forge held the identity "Jarl Brekstel" and served as the town blacksmith while Glimmerfang held the identity "Ingrid Brekstel".
{{Quote|''Friends, what my mom and dad said is true. The bravery of humankind is beyond measure.''|Razylymingeir}}
